import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

# Data buatan
penjualan = np.array([6, 5, 5, 4, 4, 3, 2, 2, 2, 1])
harga = np.array([16000, 18000, 27000, 34000, 50000, 68000, 65000, 81000, 85000, 90000])

# Visualisasi data
%matplotlib inline
plt.scatter(penjualan, harga)
plt.xlabel('Penjualan')
plt.ylabel('Harga')
plt.title('Hubungan antara Penjualan dan Harga')
plt.show()

# Membuat dan melatih model regresi
model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(penjualan.reshape(-1, 1), harga)

# Membuat prediksi
harga_prediksi = model.predict(penjualan.reshape(-1, 1))

# Visualisasi garis regresi
plt.scatter(penjualan, harga)
plt.plot(penjualan, harga_prediksi, color='red')
plt.xlabel('Penjualan')
plt.ylabel('Harga')
plt.title('Hubungan antara Penjualan dan Harga dengan Garis Regresi')
plt.show()

# Evaluasi model
print('Koefisien regresi:', model.coef_)
print('Intercept:', model.intercept_)

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error

# Data buatan
penjualan = np.array([6, 5, 5, 4, 4, 3, 2, 2, 2, 1])
penjualan = penjualan.reshape(-1, 1) # Reshape setelah definisi
harga = np.array([16000, 18000, 27000, 34000, 50000, 68000, 65000, 81000, 85000, 90000])

# Membuat dan melatih model
model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(penjualan, harga)

# Membuat prediksi
harga_prediksi = model.predict(penjualan)

# Evaluasi model
mse = mean_squared_error(harga, harga_prediksi)
print("Mean Squared Error:", mse)

# Visualisasi
plt.scatter(penjualan, harga, color='red', label='Data Aktual')
plt.plot(penjualan, harga_prediksi, color='blue', label='Garis Regresi')
plt.xlabel('Jumlah Penjualan')
plt.ylabel('Harga')
plt.title('Hubungan antara Jumlah Penjualan dan Harga')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# Cetak koefisien dan intercept
print("Koefisien regresi:", model.coef_)
print("Intercept:", model.intercept_)
Mean Squared Error: 54150000.00000002

Koefisien regresi: [-16500.]
Intercept: 109500.0

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

# Create a LinearRegression model
regr = LinearRegression()

# Prepare the training data
train_x = np.asanyarray(train[['ENGINESIZE']]) # Use double quotes for the column name
train_y = np.asanyarray(train[['CO2EMISSIONS']])

# Fit the model on the training data
regr.fit(train_x, train_y)

# Plot the training data points
plt.scatter(train['ENGINESIZE'], train['CO2EMISSIONS'], color='blue', label='Training data')

# Plot the regression line
plt.plot(train_x, regr.coef_[0][0] * train_x + regr.intercept_[0], '-r', label='Regression line')

# Add labels and title
plt.xlabel("Engine Size")
plt.ylabel("Emissions")
plt.title("Engine Size vs CO2 Emissions with Regression Line")
plt.legend() # Add a legend to the plot

# Show the plot
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
from sklearn.metrics import r2_score

# Create a LinearRegression model
regr = LinearRegression()

# Prepare the training data
train_x = np.asanyarray(train[['ENGINESIZE']]) # Use double quotes for the column name
train_y = np.asanyarray(train[['CO2EMISSIONS']])

# Fit the model on the training data
regr.fit(train_x, train_y)

# Plot the training data points
plt.scatter(train['ENGINESIZE'], train['CO2EMISSIONS'], color='blue', label='Training data')

# Plot the regression line
plt.plot(train_x, regr.coef_[0][0] * train_x + regr.intercept_[0], '-r', label='Regression line')

# Add labels and title
plt.xlabel("Engine Size")
plt.ylabel("CO2 Emissions")
plt.title("Engine Size vs CO2 Emissions with Regression Line")
plt.legend() # Add a legend to the plot

# Show the plot
plt.show()

# Prepare the test data
test_x = np.asanyarray(test[['ENGINESIZE']]) # Ensure this is the correct column name
test_y = np.asanyarray(test[['CO2EMISSIONS']]) # Ensure this is the correct column name

# Make predictions
predictions = regr.predict(test_x)

# Calculate errors
mean_absolute_error = np.mean(np.absolute(predictions - test_y))
residual_sum_of_squares = np.mean((predictions - test_y) ** 2)
r2 = r2_score(test_y, predictions)

# Print results
print("Mean absolute error: %.2f" % mean_absolute_error)
print("Residual sum of squares (RSS): %.2f" % residual_sum_of_squares)
print("R2-score: %.2f" % r2)
Mean absolute error: 22.21
Residual sum of squares (RSS): 862.34
R2-score: 0.77
